The European Community today sold181,500 tonnes of ageing butter to the Soviet Union at aspecial knockdown price, a spokesman for the EC Commissionsaid.    He said the EC's Dairy Management Committee accepted bidsfrom operators to export the butter, mainly from interventionstores in Belgium, West Germany and the Netherlands, at a priceof 21.1 European currency units per 100 kilos.    The butter was bought into Community stores at 313.2 Ecusper 100 kilos. The sales are part of the EC's process ofattempting to run down its butter surplus. REUTER&#3;